Inside the clock tower, a physiologically loathsome stench hung in the air.[p]
However, the smile of my beloved daughter in my heart lessens my uneasiness[p]
and lets me forget my fear, if even for only a moment.[p]
Reassured, I place my foot on the ladder leading underground, with my greatest motive, called love.[p]
The inside finally became a small passage about large enough for an adult.[p]
I run.[p]
Trusting that I will see her smile ahead, I run forward stomping on concrete stained with the smell of death.[p]
Once I climb the ladder at the end of the tunnel, there will be no going back.[p]
I mutter Cheryl's name one more time.[p]


